</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDDC38BBFF78F89FFEBBF95E" lastPageId="654" lastPageNumber="655" pageId="653" pageNumber="654" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDDC38B8FF78F89FFA95F99D" blockId="653.[136,778,1499,2070]" lastBlockId="653.[810,1452,1397,2070]" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDDC38B8FF78F89FFE1CF8AA" bold="true" box="[189,473,1873,1899]" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Description of female</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDC38B8FD95F89CFCC4F8AD" box="[592,769,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 444" captionStartId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" captionTargetId="figure-19@654.[136,1451,182,1421]" captionTargetPageId="654" captionText="FIGURE 444. Aplodelphys conica gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, dorsal; D, urosome, ventral; E, antenna. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Fig. 444A, B</figureCitation>
) cylindrical, consisting of unsegmented prosome and small urosome. Body length 2.29 mm in 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FEDDC38B8FDA3F858FD0EF871" box="[614,715,1942,1968]" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">holotype</typeStatus>
, 1.91 and 2.67 mm in 
<specimenCount id="9D6BFD54EDDC38B8FE93F876FE1AF813" box="[342,479,1976,2002]" pageId="653" pageNumber="654" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">2 paratypes</specimenCount>
; greatest width 0.51 mm across region of leg 1. Body surface ornamented with fine spinules. Cephalosome conical anteriorly. Posterior third of body slightly constricted, with width of 0.44 mm; posteriormargin of prosome rounded. Urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDC38B8FABBFA59FC55FA15" captionStart="FIGURE 444" captionStartId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" captionTargetId="figure-19@654.[136,1451,182,1421]" captionTargetPageId="654" captionText="FIGURE 444. Aplodelphys conica gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, dorsal; D, urosome, ventral; E, antenna. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Fig. 444C, D</figureCitation>
) small, located at posterior end of prosome, unsegmented, about twice as wide as long. Caudal rami (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDC38B8FCF7FA33FC60F9D9" box="[818,933,1533,1560]" captionStart="FIGURE 444" captionStartId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" captionTargetId="figure-19@654.[136,1451,182,1421]" captionTargetPageId="654" captionText="FIGURE 444. Aplodelphys conica gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, dorsal; D, urosome, ventral; E, antenna. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Fig. 444C</figureCitation>
) tubercle-like, spinulose, positioned on dorsal surface of urosome; lacking caudal setae. Copulatory pore positioned close to apex of urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDC38B8FB08F98FFA81F99D" box="[1229,1348,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 444" captionStartId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" captionTargetId="figure-19@654.[136,1451,182,1421]" captionTargetPageId="654" captionText="FIGURE 444. Aplodelphys conica gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, dorsal; D, urosome, ventral; E, antenna. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Fig. 444D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDDC38B8FC9AF9AAFC8AF88B" blockId="653.[810,1452,1397,2070]" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">
Rostrum and antennules absent. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDC38B8FAB8F9ADFCADF961" captionStart="FIGURE 444" captionStartId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" captionTargetId="figure-19@654.[136,1451,182,1421]" captionTargetPageId="654" captionText="FIGURE 444. Aplodelphys conica gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, dorsal; D, urosome, ventral; E, antenna. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Fig. 444E</figureCitation>
) small, 2-segmented, positioned at 18% of total body length; first segment (coxobasis) wider than long, unarmed; secondsegment (endopod) slightlylonger than wide; armed with 2 small setae distally plus stout terminal claw, half as long as endopod, with pointed tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDDC38BBFC9AF89CFE11F9BC" blockId="653.[810,1452,1397,2070]" lastBlockId="654.[136,778,1601,1696]" lastPageId="654" lastPageNumber="655" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDC38B8FC17F89CFBB9F8AD" box="[978,1148,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 444" captionStartId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" captionTargetId="figure-19@654.[136,1451,182,1421]" captionTargetPageId="654" captionText="FIGURE 444. Aplodelphys conica gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, dorsal; D, urosome, ventral; E, antenna. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Fig. 444A, B</figureCitation>
) large, conical, directed posteriorly, extendingslightlybeyond tipof leg 1; insertion of labrum at 26% of body length. No mouthparts present. Legs 1 and 2 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDDC38B8FC02F876FB9FF813" box="[967,1114,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 444" captionStartId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" captionTargetId="figure-19@654.[136,1451,182,1421]" captionTargetPageId="654" captionText="FIGURE 444. Aplodelphys conica gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, dorsal; D, urosome, ventral; E, antenna. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="653" pageNumber="654">Fig. 444A, B</figureCitation>
) biramous with unsegmented, conical, posteriorly-directed rami. Both rami equal in length; rami of leg 2 slightly smaller than those of leg 1. Legs 1 and 2 positioned at 29 and 40% of body length, respectively. Legs 3-5 absent.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655EDDF38BBFF4DFA75FBD5FA34" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592208" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592208/files/figure.png" pageId="654" pageNumber="655" startId="654.[136,240,1467,1491]" targetBox="[140,1415,210,1387]" targetPageId="654">
